definition: late last year/the end of last year

to go/to go to (a place)/(of a time etc) last/just passed/to send/to remove/to get rid of/to reduce/to be apart from in space or time/to die (euphemism)/to play (a part)/(when used either before or after a verb) to go in order to do sth/(after a verb of motion indicates movement away from the speaker)/(used after certain verbs to indicate detachment or separation)

sentences.english: At the end of last year, the company had tried to produce the one-use biodegradable corn plastic products.
sentences.chinese: 去年底，公司試生產出可降解的一次性玉米塑料產品。

sentences.english: The foot pushes off evenly at the end of the gait cycle with mild pronation.
sentences.chinese: 足部推動小康均勻，在去年底的步態週期輕旋。

sentences.english: State-owned media Xinhua reported late-last year that the trend was rising.The U.

sentences.english: Last year, our Premier Wen Jiabao paid a successful official to India.
sentences.chinese: 去年底，中國國務院總理溫家寶成功正式訪問印度。

sentences.english: Tong married Guan at the end of last year after a seven-year love marathon.(See photo)
sentences.chinese: 佟大爲和關悅經過7年愛情長跑，於去年底登記結婚。

sentences.english: But production began to slow late last year and workers drifted away.
sentences.chinese: 然而工廠的生產從去年底就放慢了，工人也開始散去。

sentences.english: As of the end of last year, Citigroup had about 147, 000 full-time employees.
sentences.chinese: 到去年底，花旗集團擁有147000名全職員工。

sentences.english: There are actually two sets of these tags, one set in the beginning and one set at the end.
sentences.chinese: 其實有兩套這些標記，一組在開始時及一組在去年底。

sentences.english: I was the end of last year to prepare for the establishment of the Shanghai venture capital companies.
sentences.chinese: 我是去年底開始去上海籌備成立創投公司的。

sentences.english: The wire mesh and center tube are epoxy-bonded to the end caps .
